Privacy policy:
Presentment clause
Your trust is very important to us. We know the importance of personal information to you. We will take corresponding security protection measures according to the requirements of laws and regulations, and try our best to protect your personal information safe and controllable. In view of this, woned formulates this Privacy Policy (hereinafter referred to as "this policy / this Privacy Policy") and reminds you that:
This policy applies to all products and services provided by woned. If woned's products or services are used in the products or services of our affiliated companies (such as logging in with woned account), but there is no independent privacy policy, this policy also applies to the products or services.
It should be noted that this policy does not apply to services provided to you by other independent third parties, nor does it apply to products or services that have separate legal statements and privacy policies in woned. For example, when a third party on woned provides services to you based on this, the personal information you provide to the third party does not apply to this privacy policy. Woned does not assume any responsibility for any third party using the information provided by you.
Before using woned's products or services, you must carefully read and thoroughly understand this policy, especially the terms marked by bold / bold underline. You should focus on reading and use relevant products or services after confirming full understanding and consent. Once you start using woned's products or services, you fully understand and agree to this policy.
Part I definition
Woned services: Based on the Internet, woned provides various services to you in various forms including woned website, client, etc. (including new service forms emerging in the future technological development).
Woned service provider: WONED TECHNOLOGY LIMITED.
User: hereinafter referred to as "you" or "user" refers to the individual or organization that registers, logs in, uses, browses and obtains services under this policy.
Personal information: information that is recorded by electronic means or other means, which can identify individual natural persons or reflect the activities of a particular natural person by combining information alone or with other information, including the name of natural person, date of birth, identity card number, personal biometric information, address, telephone number, etc.
Personal sensitive information: personal information, which is likely to cause damage to personal reputation, physical and mental health or discriminatory treatment, if it divulge, illegally provide or abuse personal and property safety, including personal identification number, personal biometric information, bank account, property information, track of whereabouts, communication content, minor information, health and physiological information, etc.
Personal information deletion: refers to the behavior of removing personal information from the system involved in the realization of daily business functions, so that it can not be retrieved and accessed.
